    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CANADIAN INFLATION INCREASES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Canada's inflation rate was stronger than expected in July, rising by 0.3 percent, to annual rate of 3 percent; Consumer Price Index rose at annual rate of only 1.5 percent in July (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Canada's inflation rate was stronger than expected in July, rising by 0.3 percent, or an annual rate of 3 percent, mainly because of higher costs for energy, food, air travel and hotels. Gasoline prices fell slightly, but hefty increases for natural gas produced a 0.9 percent rise in energy costs. Excluding food and energy, the Consumer Price Index rose at an annual rate of only 1.5 percent in July.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
